  "url": "",
  "description": "The Text DAT lets you edit free-form, multi-line ASCII text. It is used for scripts, GLSL shaders, notes, XML and other purposes. \"Free-form text\" is one of the two forms of DATs (the other being tables of rows and columns of cells, each cell containing a text string as in a Table DAT).",
  "summary": "The Text DAT lets you edit free-form, multi-line ASCII text. It is used for scripts, GLSL shaders, notes, XML and other purposes. \"Free-form text\" is one of the two forms of DATs (the other being tabl",
  "details": "",
  "usage": "",
  "tips": [
    "Text DAT is the primary container for Python scripts, GLSL shaders, and any text content.",
    "Use the edit callback to run code whenever the text is modified.",
    "Right-click and select 'Run Script' to execute Python code in a Text DAT."
  ],
